Desktop (‚â• 768px): Sidebar visible (pl-56) 4. SPACING & PADDING ANALYSIS
‚ö†Ô∏è INCONSISTENCIES FOUND:
A) Layout Padding Variations:

Layout.tsx applies:

Copy!isConversationsRoute && !isSettingsRoute && 'px-4 lg:px-6'
Regular pages: 16px mobile, 24px desktop
Conversations/Settings: NO padding (handle internally)
Page component applies:

CopyallowScroll && 'sticky top-0 bg-background z-10 px-4 lg:px-6 pt-6 pb-4'
Scrollable pages add ADDITIONAL px-4/px-6
‚ùå PROBLEM: Double padding on scrollable pages

Layout: px-4 lg:px-6
Page: px-4 lg:px-6
Result: 32px mobile, 48px desktop (TOO MUCH)
B) Common Spacing Patterns (from analysis):

Most frequent spacing utilities:

mb-4 (38 uses) - 16px bottom margin
mb-2 (29 uses) - 8px bottom margin
mr-2 (21 uses) - 8px right margin
px-4 (6 uses) - 16px horizontal padding
py-2 (9 uses) - 8px vertical padding
‚úÖ Good: Consistent use of spacing scale (2, 4, 6, 8, 12) ‚ö†Ô∏è Issue: Not using design tokens/CSS variables

C) Table Spacing Standards:

Your CSS defines:

Copy--table-cell-padding: 0.5rem 1rem; /_ 8px 16px _/
--table-row-height: 40px;
Industry Standards (from research):

Salesforce Lightning: 40-44px row height, 12-16px cell padding
HubSpot: 48px row height, 16px cell padding
Pipedrive: 40px row height, 12-16px cell padding
Attio: 40px row height, 16px cell padding
‚úÖ Your 40px row height is PERFECT - matches industry standard

