üî¥ CRITICAL ISSUES:

1. Double Padding on Scrollable Pages

Problem:

Copy// Layout.tsx adds:

<div className='px-4 lg:px-6'>
  
  // Page component adds AGAIN:
  <div className='px-4 lg:px-6 pt-6 pb-4'>
Result: 32px mobile, 48px desktop (excessive)

Fix:

Copy// Option A: Remove padding from Layout for scrollable pages
// Layout.tsx

<div className={cn(
  'flex-1 min-h-0',
  !isConversationsRoute && !isSettingsRoute && !allowScrollRoute && 'px-4 lg:px-6'
)}>

// Option B: Page component should not add padding if Layout already has it
// Check if parent has padding before adding 2. space-y-4 on Flex Containers

Problem: Using utility classes that add margin-top can interfere with min-h-0 flexbox scrolling

Fix: Use explicit margins on children instead:

Copy<div className='flex-1 flex flex-col min-h-0'>

  <div className='mb-4'><FilterControls /></div>
  <div className='flex-1 min-h-0'><UnifiedTable /></div>
  <div className='mt-4'><PaginationControls /></div>
</div>
