CONCLUSION
Your scrolling architecture is fundamentally sound and follows 2025 CRM best practices. The dual-mode system (fixed viewport for tables, natural scroll for content) is the correct approach used by Salesforce, HubSpot, and other modern CRMs.

The main issues are spacing inconsistencies that can be fixed quickly. Once the double padding issue is resolved and mobile horizontal scrolling is added, your layout will be production-ready.

The commit "fix scrolling issues - complete changes including Page component flexbox chain" (1e83ebb) shows you've already done the hard architectural work. Now it's just polish and consistency.

